In {{DefaultPullRequesrService.java}} there is a {{buildMergeMessage()}} method. The message it creates is not internationalised:

{code}
private String buildMergeMessage() {
    StringBuilder format = new StringBuilder("Merge pull request #%1$d in %3$s/%4$s from ");
    if (pullRequest.isCrossRepository()) {
        //When merging cross-repository pull requests, record the source repository in the message
        format.append("%6$s/%7$s:%8$s to %5$s");
    } else {
        //Otherwise, for intra-repository pull requests, just record the branches
        format.append("%8$s to %5$s");
    }
    if (StringUtils.isNotBlank(message)) {
        //Even if a commit message is supplied, the "Merge pull request" portion of the message is applied
        //unchanged. If a commit message is supplied, we leave a blank line between "Merge pull request"
        //and the provided message
        format.append("\n\n%2$s");
    }
    return String.format(format.toString(), pullRequest.getId(), message,
            toRef.getRepository().getProject().getKey(), toRef.getRepository().getSlug(), toRef.getDisplayId(),
            fromRef.getRepository().getProject().getKey(), fromRef.getRepository().getSlug(), fromRef.getDisplayId());
}
{code}
